</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E65CA68ECAA07168" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1966" box="[1113,1248,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Hypochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E65CA68ECAA07168" box="[1113,1248,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Hypochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E6F5A68ECBD57168" authorityName="Adams &amp; Penny" authorityYear="1992" box="[1264,1429,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Asthenochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E6F5A68ECBD57168" box="[1264,1429,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Asthenochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: proximad 
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E30FA76BCF66714C" box="[266,294,1293,1318]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">im</emphasis>
]; (3) two gradate series in radial space [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E0E8A76ACDFA714C" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2013" box="[749,954,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Okanaganochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E0E8A76ACDFA714C" box="[749,954,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Okanaganochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E1CCA76ACA18714C" authorityName="Kimmins" authorityYear="1952" box="[969,1112,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Triplochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E1CCA76ACA18714C" box="[969,1112,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Triplochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: three; 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E6ABA76ACB03714C" authorityName="Esben-Petersen" authorityYear="1917" box="[1198,1347,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Dictyochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E6ABA76ACB03714C" box="[1198,1347,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Dictyochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E757A76ACEBB7120" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Adamsochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E757A76ACEBB7120" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Adamsochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: four or more]; (4) inner gradate series of radial space arranged in smooth line [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E662A756CB417120" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1883" box="[1127,1281,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E662A756CB417120" box="[1127,1281,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E708A756CBD47120" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1883" box="[1293,1428,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Tribochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E708A756CBD47120" box="[1293,1428,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Tribochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: arranged in strongly broken line]. Hind wing: (5) MA fused with RP proximally for long distance [
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E6E8A732CBD57104" authorityName="Adams" authorityYear="1967" box="[1261,1429,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Archaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E6E8A732CBD57104" box="[1261,1429,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Archaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E292A71ECF1171F8" authorityName="Wilmann" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,337,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Stephenbrooksia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E292A71ECF1171F8" box="[151,337,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Stephenbrooksia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E35AA71ECFA971F8" authorityName="Adams &amp; Penny" authorityYear="1992" box="[351,489,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Leptochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E35AA71ECFA971F8" box="[351,489,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Leptochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: separate].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFFDFFF1E2C2A7FACB727194" blockId="19.[151,1437,1112,1787]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E2C2A7FACFD571DC" bold="true" box="[199,405,1436,1462]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Species included.</emphasis>
Five species: 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E03CA7FACA3771DC" authority="Archibald &amp; Makarkin, 2017" authorityName="Archibald &amp; Makarkin" authorityYear="2017" box="[569,1143,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E03CA7FACD6371DC" box="[569,803,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Lithochrysa borealis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFFDFFF1E12EA7FACA3771DC" author="Archibald, S. B. &amp; Makarkin, V. N." box="[811,1143,1436,1462]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="397 - 400" refId="ref22479" refString="Archibald, S. B. &amp; Makarkin, V. N. (2017) A new fossil green lacewing (Neuroptera: Chrysopidae) from the early Eocene Driftwood Canyon, Canada. Zootaxa, 4324 (2), 397 - 400. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4324.2.13" type="journal article" year="2017">Archibald &amp; Makarkin, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the early Eocene of Driftwood Canyon, 
<collectingRegion id="E71BF87AFFFDFFF1E372A7A6CC7B71B0" box="[375,571,1472,1498]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5DC87608FFFDFFF1E042A7A6CCDF71B0" box="[583,671,1472,1498]" name="Canada" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Canada</collectingCountry>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E0DDA7A7CD2171B0" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1914" box="[728,865,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wickhami">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E0DDA7A7CD2171B0" box="[728,865,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">L. wickhami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E16AA7A7CA9071B0" authority="(Cockerell, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[879,1232,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E16AA7A7CA4271B0" box="[879,1026,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">L. ferruginea</emphasis>
(Cockerell, 1909)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E6D9A7A6CB7F71B0" bold="true" box="[1244,1343,1472,1498]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">stat. res.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E748A7A7CFFA7194" authority="(Cockerell, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concinnula">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E748A7A7CEAB7194" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">L. concinnula</emphasis>
(Cockerell, 1909)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E3F0A783CC1F7194" authority="Makarkin &amp; Antell &amp; Archibald, 2022" authorityName="Makarkin &amp; Antell &amp; Archibald" authorityYear="2022" box="[501,607,1509,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meyeri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E3F0A783CC1F7194" box="[501,607,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">L. meyeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0C9857F1FFFDFFF1E063A782CC807195" box="[614,704,1508,1535]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" rank="species">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E063A782CCFA7194" bold="true" box="[614,698,1508,1534]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, all from the late Eocene of 
<collectingRegion id="E71BF87AFFFDFFF1E605A782CA2B7194" box="[1024,1131,1508,1534]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Colorado</collectingRegion>
, Florissant, 
<collectingCountry id="5DC87608FFFDFFF1E6F7A782CB6E7194" box="[1266,1326,1508,1534]" name="United States of America" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">USA</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25603698FFFDFFF1E2C2A46ECDE07248" blockId="19.[151,1437,1112,1787]" box="[199,928,1544,1571]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E2C2A46ECF127248" bold="true" box="[199,338,1544,1570]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Eocene (Ypresian to Priabonian) of North America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DC56513FFFDFFF1E2C2A44ACC367290" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25603698FFFDFFF1E2C2A44ACC367290" blockId="19.[151,1437,1112,1787]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E2C2A44ACF74722C" bold="true" box="[199,308,1580,1606]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFFDFFF1E346A44ACFA6722D" author="Adams, P. A." box="[323,486,1580,1607]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="215 - 238" refId="ref21987" refString="Adams, P. A. (1967) A review of the Mesochrysinae and Nothochrysinae (Neuroptera: Chrysopidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 135, 215 - 238." type="journal article" year="1967">Adams (1967)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E08AA44ACD55722C" authorityName="Carpenter" authorityYear="1935" box="[655,789,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E08AA44ACD55722C" box="[655,789,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Lithochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E155A44ACDAA722C" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1883" box="[848,1002,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E155A44ACDAA722C" box="[848,1002,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFFDFFF1E1FCA44ACB15722C" author="Archibald, S. B. &amp; Makarkin, V. N." box="[1017,1365,1580,1606]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="397 - 400" refId="ref22479" refString="Archibald, S. B. &amp; Makarkin, V. N. (2017) A new fossil green lacewing (Neuroptera: Chrysopidae) from the early Eocene Driftwood Canyon, Canada. Zootaxa, 4324 (2), 397 - 400. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4324.2.13" type="journal article" year="2017">Archibald &amp; Makarkin (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, however, examined new photographs of their 
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFFDFFF1E06DA437CCD87201" box="[616,664,1617,1643]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E0FBA437CA147200" authority="(Cockerell, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[766,1108,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wickhami">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E0FBA437CDC77200" box="[766,903,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">L. wickhami</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFFDFFF1E193A436CA0C7200" author="Cockerell, T. D. A." box="[918,1100,1616,1642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="714 - 724" refId="ref23258" refString="Cockerell, T. D. A. (1914) New and little-known insects from the Miocene of Florissant, Colorado. Journal of Geology, 22, 714 - 724. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 622186" type="journal article" year="1914">Cockerell, 1914</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E68FA437CBD87200" authority="Scudder, 1890" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1890" box="[1162,1432,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stricta">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E68FA437CAAE7200" box="[1162,1262,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">P. stricta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="414E4B69FFFDFFF1E6F0A436CBD87200" author="Scudder, S. H." box="[1269,1432,1616,1642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 734" refId="ref25710" refString="Scudder, S. H. (1890) The Tertiary insects of North America. Report of the United States Geological Survey of the Territories, 13, 1 - 734, 28 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 44698" type="journal article" year="1890">Scudder, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and found them clearly distinguished: in both the fore- and hind wings of 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E1E2A412CAEC72E5" authority=", Psm" authorityName="Psm" box="[999,1196,1652,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E1E2A412CA2D72E4" box="[999,1133,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Lithochrysa</emphasis>
, Psm
</taxonomicName>
is poorly developed, strongly zigzagged, and the crossveins of the inner gradate series are arranged in a smooth line, but in 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFDFFF1E6FEA4FECE8772BD" authority=", Psm" authorityName="Psm" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFDFFF1E6FEA4FECBD572D8" box="[1275,1429,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Palaeochrysa</emphasis>
, Psm
</taxonomicName>
is well developed, very slightly zigzagged (especially in the hind wing), and the crossveins of the inner gradate series are arranged in strongly broken line.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
